  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening the Health Capacities in Greek Reception and Identification Centers (RICs)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will contribute to the efforts of the Greek authorities in addressing the health needs of migrants living in the Greek islands of Lesvos, Samos, Chios, Leros and Kos and easing the health burden on the local health services. To this end, IOM will strengthen the diagnostic capacities of the biochemistry laboratory and radiological facility in the five (5) Reception and Identification Centres (RICs) on the aforementioned islands through the provision of technical (medical teams) and logistical support (ambulances and essential medical equipment and supplies). Through the proposed activities, IOM aims particularly at relieving the burden of the national health care system and reinforcing the national health actor that does not have sufficient capacity to serve the RICs&#x2019; medical caseload due to limited resources, coupled with COVID-19 restrictions and limitations. Ultimately, the project will enhance the health and well-being of migrants residing in RICs, while also supporting other operational aspects (such as RICs&#x2019; decongestion) related to the management of RICs by the responsible Greek authority (RIS).</narrative>
  </description>
